The Yoruba Community in Maiduguri, under the leadership of the Oba ( Mai ) Yoruba of Borno, Alhaj Hassan Alao Yusuf, yesterday organized an interfaith prayer programme to pray for return of peace in Borno state . The group also prayed for God’s protection over Governor Babagana Umara Zulum, as he selflessly and courageously takes steps to better the lives of citizens of Borno state and return the millions of displaced people back to their ancestral homes. Speaking during the prayer session, Otunba Lanre Obadiah explained that Yorubas in the state regard Borno as their home ,having lived there for decades and therefore see themselves as stakeholders in the well being of the state. He reiterated their support for Governor Babagana Umara Zulum and their concern for his safety as he confronts the hydra headed monster of insurgency with unprecedented courage and determination. Otumba Obadiah, who is also the Senior Special Assistant on Publicity to Governor Zulum also expressed the view that prayer is the greatest weapon the Yoruba’s can deploy to support Governor Zulum in his fight against the insurgency. In a key note address, the Oba Yoruba of Borno, Alhaji Hassan Alao Yusuf , had called on all Yoruba in Borno to constantly put in their prayers, for the governor, Shehu of Borno and all people in Borno, both indigenes and non indigenes so that peace will reign in the land and the people will prosper. Other speakers include Professor Ohu of the University Maiduguri, the President of the Yoruba Community Council, Alhaji Tahiru and a woman leader, Hajiya Mulikat Sanni. Extensive prayers were then rendered by both muslim and Christian clerics. End